<br>
This notion that mages are some sort of overpowered gods just isnt true. The theory that Verant will do nothing to increase solo power just isnt true. They have done it multiple times giving snare to wizards, 70% bindwounds to all melee, 50% slow to necromancers and the list goes on and on. The idea that we cant be great solo, on raids and in groups just isnt true. Monks, Druids, Wizards all have great solo ability, raid ability and group ability. <br>
<br>
Every class post 50 begins to seperate from the pack in terms of there defining abilities.  Wizards become the best DD class pulling futher away from druids and mages. The cleric's healing power becomes overwhelming post 50 so much so that no one would ever dream of taking another healer class over a cleric under most conditions. Shamans become the masters of slowing and wearing mobs down. Druids becoming without a doubt the best multi-purpose casting class in the game.  The list goes on and on....the problem is mages dont become best at anything. Alot of people will say we are the masters of summoning but that is like saying enchanters are the masters of alteration it really means nothing. Our pets dont move ahead of the pack it is just the opposite the pack moves closer to elemental pets. Emissary of Thule can kill any mage pet but the GV earth without damage shield (not including epic pet).<br>
<br>
The truth is there are a ton of ways to increase mage damage output without stepping on the toes of other classes. 1250 to 1300dd nuke based on our shock of blades line. A summoned stone that fits in the range slot that gives 3hp/mana regen and has a 51+ cap on it so no one lower then that can use it.  A line of spells based on the sword of runes.  Swords that proc 30% slow, a sword that procs the lvl 8 shock spell, or a sword that a mage can summon at lvl 60 that allows the pet to proc a 150heal. Also lure based swords have already been talked about a ton.  Beastlords can give there pets a unresistable DD proc at lvl 52.  A 50hp damage shield at lvl 60.  Enchanters get a version at lvl 60 of the spell that is on there epic. Why cant we have a spell we can cast that is equal or better then our epic pets damage shield. A new pet buff that increases atk,str.  Summon Gate potions that will send people back to there bind points. Summon a stone that is lore and no drop with one charge of divine aure/harmshield on it. They can make the mana cost high but at least when we need a quick escape we can attempt a run to the zone.  At lvl 60 summoned orb that has 3 charges of the lvl 44 dd spell on it for 500mana.  Lastly a stackable damage shield. That does 20damage and stacks. I mean if you have 5 mages then they can all add a 20hp stackable damage shield to all the groups. That would be 100 extra damage per group.<br>
<br>
I am not saying all of the above items are good ideas or even that all mages would like them. What I am saying is there are alot of ways to improve the class via the summoning line if they really wanted to make the class worthwhile again without stepping on other classes toes. I personally think mages are a great group class...would be nice to be able to add something other then damage when I group. If the normal 6 man group there is almost never a need for mod rods or CoTH.  Also making our post lvl 50 fire pets like the pre 50 fire pets would be great also.<br>
