<br>
The hypothetical magician hybrid cannot (according to VI) be allowed to have a pet whose tanking ability aprioaches or surpasses high level pure melees. And its a fair enough conclusion: that is after all all that they do, bash things.<br>
<br>
Similar case for Wizards. What they do, at the core of their class, is blow things up. Closing the gap bvetween mages and wizards is not likely to happen.<br>
<br>
Hence my conclusion that our only class-defining ability (summoning stuff) is the only avenue remaining for magicians to stamp their mark on the end game.<br>
<br>
My question is, how? <p><center><embed width="520" height="120" loop=false src="http://www.aus-1.au.nu/Movie1.swf"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyalur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(2/12/02 2:44:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  master of pets!</span><hr size=1> what the mage class should be is the master of pets !!<br>
<br>
if u take a look at all the classes with pets mages are the only one who rely on them badly. a mage without a pet is a dead mage. all other classes have means of surviving without pets, only we lack it.<br>
<br>
so all we need is better pet control (and a bit stronger ones past 50 too)<br>
<br>
i think about a mindlink skill, which gives us better control over the pet. but with some drawbacks of course.<br>
first: during the mindlink the mage can not move and at lower lvls NOT cast too. later (maybe 35 when the book is gone) we should be allowed to cast spells.<br>
<br>
the mindlink should increase the range of all pet commands dramaticaly, since theres no need to shout.<br>
and there should be a mindlink only use command /pet stay on target !!! even if other mobs hit it. now the major drawback of the skill is, the mage takes a percentage of damage the pet recieves during the mindlink. (which should decrease with higher skill too)<br>
thus the skill will not overpower us at all, when we solo, we take damage when more mobs trash the pet. but in a group the pet can be used!<br>
<br>
well thats the idea, and since i think we dont get better nukes or pets --- but i hope more usefull summon spells -- a skill to control pets like no other class (but doesnt give us more power in any case) is what we need !<br>
<br>
ahh yes and the skill should start at lvl 4, when we can summon pets !<br>
