<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: master of pets!</span><hr size=1> First off, I'd like to agree that based on the ability to melee and do magical damage (through various means), it would seem as though Magicians are a nice hybrid between a melee class (warror/weak rogue, depending on pet) and a weak wizard. Individually, these things are pathetic compared to others, but together, they're quite handy to have, and quite strong.<br>
<br>
/em braces himself.<br>
<br>
First off, it is my humble opinion that having the strongest pet and being a master of pets are not necessarily the same concept. Besides, the term &quot;pet&quot; can be applied to many different creatures. We are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Masters of Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, in a fashion, as well as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Masters of Summoning/Creation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I say 'in a fashion' because while we can summon elementals and have (usually) supurb mastery over them, we cannot command elementals that we did not summon ourselves (via charm). And, while some might argue of the usefullness of our summons, I find some of them rather usefull.<br>
<br>
If you want to be a Master of (a) Pet, might try a Beastlord. They can do more for their pets than we Magicians can. Of course, they don't have pets as strong as ours, but still.<br>
<br>
As for.. Wezloc.. man, I read through your post, and saw two statements that just blew my mind away.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Both of those classes can do what they do best to a insane degree. So much so they make alot of small group encounters trivial.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
(in talking about Shaman slowing and Cleric healing) A cleric's healing abilities and a shaman's debuff/slowing abilities are often refered to as &quot;usefull skills&quot;. Now, they may be the best at what they do &quot;to an insane degree&quot;, but a shaman slowing something comes at a high risk in high end encounters. Love to watch a Shaman slow (and land successfully) only to get summoned and summerily killed. As for clerics, what else are they going to contribute if not for healing in all it's varied forms?<br>
<br>
I don't think they make many small group encounters trivial. Easier, yes, but groups with Clerics and Shaman still die, and can easily get swamped.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I feel the same should be done to our summon line of spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Right here, the next statement, I have to question your whole thinking process. You feel that Clerics and Shaman make some encounters trivial, so you feel that our summon spells should also make some encounters trivial. What's the point then? Is it going to make it more fun for you to be able to walk through more encounters now because your presence there makes them trivial? I'd rather have &quot;tough, but managable&quot;, myself.<br>
<br>
I can spell something out for you in simple english about Verant, and what they'll do to balance us out. Rather, what they won't do.<br>
<br>
Verant will not give us spells/summons/abilities that will make encounters trivial.<br>
<br>
In fact, they're taking away usefullness of spells because of making new things (same ol' same ol') trivial.<br>
<br>
Now, I wouldn't mind more usefull summons, don't get me wrong there. I figure we've managed to survive this long without Bind/Gate stones, or stun, or root, or lotsa other spells that we really don't need them, in my opinion. Bind/gate stones might be a nice luxury item, but what use would I have for root? I have my pet, let it kick said mob's rear and hold it in place.<br>
<br>
I don't think we should be at a point where we deal as much damage as rogues (since we have pretty decent utility at high end). It would be nice to be able to contribute damage through my most usefull asset, my pet. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
